<div class="recipe-container">
    <h1>Mixed Rice Recipe</h1>

    <div class="recipe-description">
        <p><strong>Mixed Rice</strong> is a delicious and flavorful South Indian dish made by mixing cooked rice with a variety of spices, vegetables, and seasonings. It is an easy and quick meal, perfect for lunchboxes or a wholesome meal.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ingredients">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <div class="ingredient-list">
            <div class="ingredient-item">
                <p><strong>Main Ingredients:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups Cooked rice (preferably cooled)</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Oil or Ghee</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Mustard seeds</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Cumin seeds</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Peanuts or Cashews</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric powder</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Red chili powder</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Garam masala</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Asafoetida (Hing)</li>
                    <li>Salt to taste</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="ingredient-item">
                <p><strong>Vegetables (Optional, for added flavor):</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>1/4 cup Carrot (grated or finely chopped)</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Green beans (finely chopped)</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Bell peppers (diced)</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Green peas</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp Coriander leaves (chopped)</li>
                    <li>1 Green chili (slit)</li>
                    <li>Curry leaves (a few)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cooking-instructions">
        <h2>How to Cook</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Prepare the Rice:</strong> Cook the rice and let it cool to prevent it from becoming sticky.</li>
            <li><strong>Tempering:</strong> Heat oil in a pan. Add mustard seeds and cumin seeds. Once they splutter, add peanuts or cashews and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li><strong>Add Vegetables:</strong> Add chopped green chilies, curry leaves, carrots, beans, bell peppers, and peas. Sauté for 2-3 minutes.</li>
            <li><strong>Spice it Up:</strong> Add turmeric, red chili powder, garam masala, asafoetida, and salt. Mix well.</li>
            <li><strong>Mix the Rice:</strong> Add the cooked rice and mix gently, ensuring that the rice is coated well with the spices.</li>
            <li><strong>Garnish & Serve:</strong> Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and serve hot.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="tips">
        <h2>Tips & Variations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>For added crunch, sprinkle roasted peanuts on top before serving.</li>
            <li>You can replace regular rice with brown rice or quinoa for a healthier version.</li>
            <li>Add 1 tsp lemon juice for a tangy flavor.</li>
            <li>Try variations like tomato rice, coconut rice, or lemon rice by changing a few ingredients.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="serve">
        <h2>Serving Suggestions</h2>
        <p>Serve Mixed Rice hot with raita, papad, or pickle for a delicious and complete meal.</p>
    </div>
</div>
